"* 15. (95) The sketch shows the outline of a building. The peak of the roof is 16 feet above the ground. What is the volume of the building? (Hint: Divide the figure into a rectangular prism and a triangular prism.) 16. (46) Find the total cost, including 6 percent sales tax, of 2 tacos at $2.25 each, 2 fruit drinks at $1.20 each, and a salad at $1.30. * 17. (94) a. Analyze There are two red, three white, and four blue marbles in a bag. If Chad pulls two marbles from the bag, what is the probability that one will be white and the other blue? b. Explain Will the order of the draws affect the probability. Support your answer. 18. (84, 87) Simplify: a. (−2xy)(−2x)(x2y) b. 6x − 4y + 3 − 6x − 5y − 8 19. (83) Multiply. Write the product in scientific notation. (8 × 10−6)(4 × 104) * 20. (56, Inv. 9) a. Use the function rule to complete the table. b. Graph the function. c. Analyze At what point does the graph of the function intersect the y axis? 21. (40) Find the measures of the following angles. 55° x 110° y D B E A C a. ∠x b. ∠y c. ∠A 22. (78) Represent On a number line, graph all the negative numbers that are greater than −2. 23. (34) What is the average of the numbers labeled A and B on the number line below? 1.5 A 1.6 B Saxon Math Course 2 y  1 2 x  1 x y −2 30 ft 10 ft 40 ft"
